name: Waffle House
directions: Just walk in go to the left.
comment: I'm ftm pre-T/pre-op, and I've been using this bathroom without any problems for a couple years now whenever I go to Crossroads.  Just go in and do your thing.  They shouldn't ask questions, but if they do, just say you have to use the bathroom.  A lot of truckers stop there, so they're used to it (people just using their bathroom, not eating).

name: Hookah Bookah Cafe
directions: Two locking bathrooms on the left: women's near the middle, men's by the counter.

name: Colorado State University
directions: 1st floor of the Gifford Building, SouthWest Corner.  Labled as 'Staff Restroom' but is available to anyone.  Street parking is free.  If you do not have a parking permit do not park in the parking lots.

name: Whole Foods
directions: Near the Jamba Juice area in the right part of the store. There are two bathrooms, both gender neutral, both single occupancy rooms.

name: Third Chapter Tattoo
directions: Go in the front door, down the stairs, take a right down the hallway, and there are two single stall, locking bathrooms, one with a picture of James Dean and one with a picture of Marilyn Monroe.
comment: Third Chapter is does quality tattoo work and is also very queer friendly. they share the building with a smoke shop in the other suite, the bathrooms are available whenever the building is open, but you don't actually have to go into the smoke shop or Third Chapter to get to them.

name: Nova Cafe
directions: Towards the back of the restaurant and to the right down a hallway. Two single stall, locking bathrooms, one marked 'either' the other marked 'or.'
comment: Nova Cafe is great and super queer friendly!

name: University Center, Carnegie Mellon University
directions: In the basement, there are two unisex, single-seat restrooms in the foyer to the Prayer Room.  Follow the signs for the prayer room and you'll see them on your left.

name: Airport Rd/Mall/Barnes and Noble
street: Airport Rd Across from Sacred Heart and RAVE theater
directions: Back by the music area. Look for sign high on the wall.
comment: 9 am to 11 pm

directions: 1)RCH (JR Coutts Engineering Lecture Hall): basement / lower floor.  There's a single-stall wheelchair accessible washroom across from the water fountain & vending machines.2) SLC: there are two gender-neutral accessible bathrooms on the main floor right beside Tim Hortons.3) ENVIRONMENT 2: on the ground floor, down a side hallway where the research labs are. Unmarked door, single stall. Has a grab bar but it\\'s a tiny space and the door is heavy.4) ENVIRONMENT 1: on the top floor (where rooms start with a 3). Gender-neutral. Fully accessible, but the elevator in that building is sketchy.
comment: The Glow Centre used to put out a list of gender-neutral/single-stall bathrooms on campus. The list doesn\\\\\\'t seem to be on their website, but you could email them or ask at the Centre for one (SLC 2101).

name: Fair Grounds Coffee
directions: Upstairs in FairGrounds Coffee, to the left of the straws, napkins, and stirrers

name: IIT/Life Sciences Building
directions: There is a bathroom marked 'MENS' on the basement floor - this one is actually gender-neutral. On the first floor or second floor (can't remember right now), there is a bathroom that is marked for both.
comment: Life Sciences Building is only for use by IIT Students, Faculty, and Staff. However, you do not specifically need to show an ID to use the bathroom. The one in the basement might get you looked at oddly, since it is not as well known that it is for all genders.

name: Lilly Library
directions: 1st floor, down the hallway behind the circulation desk on the left (south) side.
comment: Mon.-Thurs. 8am - 2amFri. 8am - midniteSat. 9am - midniteSun. 10am - 2amParking is only legal on the weekend and on weekdays after 6pm, so be quick.

name: Dunkin Donuts
comment: Single locking bathroom

name: Ocean Coffee Roasters
directions: Back of restaurant
comment: Awesome Coffee

name: Public toilets
directions: Between convenience store & sunglasses store in parking lot.
comment: Public toilet

name: Pub on Pearl
directions: In the back, past the pool tables.

name: Cherry Creek Mall
directions: Lower level, right next to the gendered ones.
comment: It's officially a family room.

name: Game Empire
directions: Dead ahead from the entrance, pretty easy to see.
comment: Open until 10 PM, seven days a week.This is a gaming store, people!  There's more for board games and card games and puzzles than for computer games, though there's very lively war games at times.

name: 5710 LGBTQ and multicultural student center
directions: gender-neutral bathrooms on first and third floors, along with single-sex restrooms.

name: Green Hall, UChicago campus
directions: it's on the first floor. turn left after coming in the front door and it's about 3 doors down the hall.
comment: the building closes at night.

name: Satori Coffee HOUSE
comment: Great coffee too!

name: Valley Art Association
directions: All the way in the back, easy enough to find or the old ladies who work there will tell you.
comment: Check them online for hours, they vary.

name: Izgara
directions: You can ask for directions, but the toilets are up the sloped hallway in the back of the restaurant, turn left, turn left again.
comment: Amazing food, open pretty late.

name: BJ's Coffee Co.
directions: Around, past the last table and the end of the counters, there are two bathrooms (no gender, locking door on each), the most accessible one is directly to your left.  There is another that is all the way at the end of the mini-hall, to your right (NOT the door directly ahead, that is to the outside).
comment: Good coffee and lots of fun candy.

name: Maggie's Buns
directions: It's the chalkboard-painted door right behind the register counter.
comment: Their coffee is pretty good (but heavy on syrup) as are their (fresh made) sandwiches, but don't get food from the cooler, it's a refrigeration roulette for your tummy.

name: Slingshot Lounge
directions: There are two looking, genderfree bathrooms in the back across from the kitchen. The first of the two is accessible.
comment: You won't find a better bar, with better staff or better food, in all of FoPo. The prices are very reasonable ($1.00 Oly pints during happy hour) and the regulars are all super friendly.

name: The Bean Counter
directions: Straight in and to the left.

name: Pick'n Save
directions: Enter store and look for the check out. The bathrooms are immediately across from the registers
comment: Thanks for being tidy.  Have a nice day

name: Wal-Mart
directions: Enter store and walk straight to back of the store.
comment: Thanks for being tidy.  Enjoy an \"old school\" small Wal-Mart.

name: Viking Park
directions: Enter Viking Park parking on the west side of HWY N and look for a small tan building about 100' due west of the parking lot.
comment: Thanks for being tidy. Bring your dog(s) and enjoy the off-leash dog park.

name: One World Café
directions: From front entrance, go in past the bar and turn left; from side entrance, go straight ahead.
comment: Excellent vegetarian/vegan food with fast and friendly service.  Ask about their house-made veggie burger of the day.

name: New Deal Cafe
directions: Towards the back to the right of the cashier.

name: Q Center
directions: Through front door go right past lounge area. Go through door on right (Bathrooms are shared w/ other businesses). Walk down hallway. Two bathrooms on left.

name: Amnesia Brewing
directions: Two bathrooms in the back to the right of the bar.

name: OHSU (Physicians Pavilion )
street: Physicians pavilion 3147 S.W. Sam Jackson Park Rd
directions: Walk straight through front door to elevator. Go to the 3rd floor. Go right out of elevator. The cooridor bends left go straight. Two bathrooms on left.

name: Green River Coffee Co.
directions: Walk in front door, turn left, walk forward, and bathroom will be on your right. Two bathrooms.
comment: Gay friendly staff!

name: Mr. Yogato
directions: Bathroom is in the back of the shop (the common area labeled 'The Park'), straight back from the front door.

name: Pittsburgh Mills Mall Movie Theater
directions: Men's, Women's, & Family bathrooms in the movie theater.
comment: I always use the family bathroom and have never had a problem.

name: Target
comment: Gender neutrual Family bathroom, right by service desk

name: Steinbeck Library
directions: walk in the front door, turn right walk passed the computer lab. turn right again and walk through the glass door.

name: The Howard County Visitors Information Center
directions: Located in the basement of the old post office.

name: BMC Diner
directions: There is a pair of gendered, single-seat restrooms in the back, down a hallway to the left of the kitchen entrance.
comment: It's a restaurant.  You'll probably want to buy something.  It may be named something other than the \"BMC Diner\" by the time you get there; in the two decades my family's been going on vacation near it, it's had three different owners.

name: Rangeley Public Library
directions: There is a single 'family' restroom in the back near the computer area.
comment: The library is not open on Mondays, and doesn't have particularly long hours.  Check the sign.

name: Java Joe's Corner Cafe
directions: There's one genderfree bathroom in the back of the store, labelled 'Yes, this is the restroom!'
comment: Seems like a fairly progressive place.

name: First Congregational Church of Wilton Maine UCC
directions: To the left from the 'church offices' entrance, past the parlor.

name: Calvary Church
directions: There are two gender-free but multi-stall (i.e., coed) restrooms in the basement.  Not sure about other floors.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: In the back, past the greeting cards

name: Pazzos
directions: Walk in the front entrance and the bathroom is right next to the bar on the right. The restrooms are gendered and multi stalled and one of them requires you to go down the stairs into the basement and doesnt seem terribly safe.Also, these restrooms are NOT single stall. They are multistall.
comment: Also, there isn't a single bathroom there where you don't have to go down at least a few stairs so they're not accessible.

name: Dunn Bros
directions: Back of the building, down the stairs.

name: Macalester College Campus Center
directions: Lower level.  Turn left at the bottom of the stairs, the bathroom is on your left.

name: Milwaukee LGBT Community Center
directions: All three bathrooms within the Center are Genderfree.  Two are multiple-stall (2 stalls in each), and one is a single-stall, accessible restroom.
comment: The Center is open:Mon        10am-5pmTue-Thur   10am-9pmFri        10am-10pmSat        6-10pm

name: Geckos Bar
directions: Must be 21 or with a parent to enter this business.

name: Walmart
directions: Family bathroom near layaway counter.

name: University of New Meixco WRC Mesa Vista Hall
directions: Mesa Vista Hall is east of the Student Union Bldg. The WRC is on the east entrance near the Student Health Center parking lot.
comment: Hours vary, but are posted at the beginning of each semester.

name: Isotopes Park
directions: Near the 3rd base concessions is a single use family bathroom available for anyone to use.

name: starbucks
directions: corner of pioneer and main
comment: very friendly place

name: Place Bonaventure
directions: Inside place bonaventure. One on the basement floor at Metro Level follow signs to the food court there`s a handicap private stallalso on the 4th floor of S-E tour there`s another one.

name: Dunkin Donuts
comment: There's only one bathroom in the place and it has the man/woman sign.

name: Tenderloin Self Help Center
directions: Turk & Hyde St.

name: Jewel-Osco
directions: Walk in any door, go right all the way to photo counter/liquor section, bathrooms on far end of photo counter.
comment: Open 7 days a week till midnight, opens most days at 6am. - (847) 381-4525

name: Twelve Pine
comment: Two nice genderfree one-seaters!

name: 61C Cafe
directions: in the back of the coffee shop, 2 unisex, single stall bathrooms.
comment: nice place to read a book, too.

name: Ugly Mug Coffee Shop
directions: All the way in the back of the shop
comment: A very small bathroom, single stall/locking with no gender specification

name: Coffee Tree Roasters
directions: Straight back past the counter
comment: Queer friendly area, baristas are generally queer/queer friendly.

name: Jersey Shore Premium Outlets
directions: This outlet center has 5 sets of restrooms, one in each group of buildings and one in the food court.  Each set of restroom contains mens, ladies and family restrooms.
comment: I have used the family restrooms many times an never encountered a problem.

name: Cumberland Farms
directions: To the end of the building
comment: 24/7/365 Overall clean and a place to go and fill up

name: OPC
directions: On every floors - this is an older persons' center, so there are a lot of them :-)

name: Rochester Hills Public Library
directions: Two on the main floor, West entrance. Two or more upstairs.
comment: Library hours. Mon - Sat. 9:00 - 9:00, Sept- May open on Sunday 1 - 5

name: Florida State University
directions: Psychology department.  Go in the front door, down the steps.  It's right next to the gendered bathrooms on the 1st floor.
comment: Building is open 8am until around 6 or 7pm

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: Go to the far right corner of the store after you go in the front door. It's right by the Kombucha & Coffee bar
comment: It's in a small hallway in a corner of the store, so not many people will see you using the bathroom. Both the women's and men's bathrooms are single-stall.

name: Prescott College
directions: To the left of the cafe at the crossroads center. the cafe, by the way, has great vegan/gluten free/ etc food when they are open...prescott.edu

name: Rock Paper Scissors
directions: in the back right-hand corner
comment: open wed-sun 12-7

name: Chick-Fil-A
directions: There is a seating area to the right of the front counter/registers. In the back is an opening in the wall near the right side. The men and womens restrooms are located here.
comment: These are usually pretty clean, even during peak hours (7:00-8:30 and 5:00-7:30)

name: Bar Of the Gods (BOG)
directions: Take a left through the front door and they are in the back by the pool table. the 'womens' is labled Godess the 'mens' is across from it and is not labled.

name: Central Square Station
directions: It is on the outbound side of the platform. You have to pay fare to go inside.
comment: Open until the time the subway closes.

name: Woburn Public Library
directions: First Floor
comment: It is a library so you should be slightly quiet.

name: Baltimore Aquarium
directions: On the first floor of the aquarium there is a family bathroom in between the other two.

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: In the far left of the building after entering either main doors, past the floral counter and between the prepared foods area and the Salud! cooking classroom.
comment: The store is open all day every day (except Christmas) from 7:00am to 10:00pm, and the bathrooms are open to the public. It's obviously good manners to buy something if you want to pee there, but the last time I checked it wasn't required - and nobody even notices if you don't.

name: House Laundry & Dry Cleaning
directions: Access from Basin street and Alder. Walk forward from either door. Middle of the building. Toilet, sink and outlet. No soap, baby changer or towels. Cold water only.
comment: Doors lock at 11pm. Old and dirty - but the door lock still works. Snack, soda pop, change, and detergent machine in building. Dry Cleaning service no longer available.Available outlets in bathroom and behind snack vending machine.

name: Lowes
directions: The bathrooms are in the front of the store. There are large open gendered bathrooms, but just to the right of the entrance for the mens is a genderfree single-use bathroom

name: State Theatre
directions: To the right of the front doors, at the base of the stairs.
comment: You usually have to have a ticket to a movie to use this restroom, however, if you ask they may let you in to use it without a ticket. It is a single use, accessible gender-free restroom.

name: The Wedge
directions: From the front door, make a right along the front windows and there are two bathrooms down at the end (under the sign saying Restrooms).

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: Two genderfree single-room restroom on ground floor, to the right of the check-out lines.
comment: Chain supermarket specializing in holistic/organic/fair trade groceries.

name: XS
directions: Ground floor, in the back
comment: Casual-hip fusion cafe/diner with decent sushi and coffee, vegetarian-friendly menu and very nice house-made desserts.  Open 7am to Midnight Monday through Thursday, 7am to 2am Friday through Saturday, and 9am to Midnight on Sundays.

name: The Center Project
directions: This is a GLBT Community Center
comment: Open from 3pm till 7pm to the public 7 days a week.

name: Albertson's
comment: 5am-12am daily

name: Gas Station
street: 7th St. and Eastern Ave., Off Exit 113 from I-40

name: FourBarrel Coffee
directions: at the back of the cafe, behind the bar area. or just ask, people are very friendly here.

name: Stout Brothers Pub and Restaurant
directions: Right next to the backdoor.
comment: Great food, great pub atmosphere, and a single stall, gender-free bathroom.

name: texas roadhouse
directions: Back left corner of restraunt says 'out house' above it in big lights
comment: Very clean

name: Cloud City Coffee
street: Corner of NE 88th St. & Roosevelt Way NE
comment: 6am-7pm summer, 6am-6pm winter, free wifi, great pastriesm, breakfast and lunch items, LGBTQ friendly
